value: Breeds locally on the arctic coasts and islands of the Holarctic region in Greenland, Iceland, Spitsbergen, and Novaya Zemlya; from the mouth of the Yenessei to the Chukchi Peninsula; New Siberian Islands; west coast of Alaska south to the Yukon Delta; extreme northwestern Alaska to Southampton Island, north to Melville Island and Ellesmere Island; southeastern Baffin Island. Winters at sea off the west coast of Africa and coast of Chile.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Palearctic winter visitor, sea: off Mauritania to Ghana and Namibia; rare inland (records Kenya to South Africa).
Wet coastal tundra (breeding); in winter, primarily pelagic, most commonly at upwellings; occurring in migration on bays and estuaries, less frequently on ponds, lakes, and marshes.
